  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Before you begin, make the No-Fuss Roast Chicken."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Preheat the oven to 190°C."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Roughly chop the fennel bulb and onion. Preheat a medium-sized, oven-proof frying pan over a medium heat. Add a good glug of oil and tip in the chopped veggies. Add a pinch of salt and cook for 4-5 mins until starting to soften. Add the cumin and turmeric and cook for a minute. Slice the garlic clove and tip into the pan. Cook for 2-3 mins together before adding the chicken stock and the jar of chickpeas, liquid and all. Bring to a boil and reduce by about a third."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Cut the chicken into bite-sized pieces and stir through the stew with the olives. Roughly chop half of the parsley (stalks and all!) and add to the stew. Have a taste and adjust the seasoning, adding a little lemon juice if you’d like."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Lay the sheets of filo out and brush with olive oil. Scrunch them into little bundles and sit on top of your stew. Slide into the oven for 18-20 mins or until the pastry is golden and crisp."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Combine the leaves from the remaining parsley in a bowl with thinly sliced red onion and the juice of the lemon. Toss with a little olive oil and salt. Serve the crispy filo stew on warm plates with a big handful of parsley salad."
    }
  ],
